title: Alpha particle induced reactions on natSb and 121Sb with particular reference to the production of the medically interesting radionuclide

with particular reference to the production of the
medically interesting radionuclide

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Applied Radiation and Isotopes, Vol.64, p.101 (2006)

x4freetext: CV28 compact cyclotron
High purity 99.9999% natural Sb from Sigma-Aldrich
High purity (99%) and 99.45% enriched 121Sb from Oak
Ridge.
Al and Ti foils for beam monitoring from Goodfellow.
Sedimentation technique was used for sample preparation
in which 7 mm in diameter of Sb layer was prepared
onto 127 micron thick Ti backing. The thickness of the
Sb layer was 4-10mg/cm2 and was covered 10micron thick
Al foil. Samples were Al-Sb-Ti sandwich.
Irradiation was done in Faraday-cup target
holder with 26 MeV He-4 beam at CV28 compact cyclotron.
Several stack were irradiated for 2h with 100nA beam.
HPGe detector was used.
Stopping and energy degradation were calculated using
the stopping power tables of Williamson.
Primary energy was determined by TOF method.
